Phoenix::

"Thanks," she says, and heads off.  She's good enough at following 
directions that she doesn't take any wrong turns.  Just before she 
slips into the CR, she shudders.  She really doesn't care for these 
things - nor did she care for the way Switchblade looked at her.  She 
is seriously beginning to doubt her chances that life among the 
Predacons will be much better than that with the Rogues.

Putting it out of her mind, she relaxes and lets the machine do its 
work.

--- In nbwrpg@y..., "x_rauq_x" <x_rauq_x@y...> wrote:
> -- Switchblade --
> 
> Switchblade glances over Pheonix, staring at her intensely. His gaze 
> rakes over her slowly, then he looks away, to the front of the 
> control room.
> 
> "Computer, display the nearest path from control room to the CR 
> chambers." The computer obliges him, and a small map appears.
> 
> He shrugs, the speaks again, "Follow the path; don't get lost." Two 
> dots light up on the map, a green glowing dot for Switchblade, and a 
> dull reddish dot for Pheonix.
